headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 29 points and 11 assists and the Detroit Pistons won for the seventh time it their last eight road games, 114-104 over the Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cade Cunningham scores 29 points to lead Pistons past cold-shooting Hawks

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 32 points in his 200th career 30-point performance, Kevin Durant added 24 against his...
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker and Durant lead the Suns to a 108-84 victory over the short-handed Nets

headlines.description: — Jaden McDaniels scored a career-high 27 points, including the clinching free throw with 3 seconds to play, and Anthony Edwards added 21 as the Minnesota Timberwolves outlasted the short-handed Dallas Mavericks 115-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaden McDaniels goes for career-high 27 points as Wolves outlast Mavs 115-114

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun made two free throws with 4.5 seconds left and Darius Garland missed two of three free throws after that to allow the Houston Rockets to hold on for a 109-108 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun makes late free throws and Garland misses 2 as Rockets outlast Cavs, 109-108

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 24 points, Luke Kennard added 23 on a season-high seven 3-pointers and the Memphis Grizzlies built an early lead and beat the Charlotte Hornets 132-120 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane, Kennard help the Grizzlies build early lead in 132-120 victory over the Hornets

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New Orleans Pelicans
Utah Jazz at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored a career-high 54 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Utah Jazz 123-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores career-high 54 in Thunder's 123-114 win over Jazz

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 32 points, Domantas Sabonis had 26 points and 18 rebounds and the Sacramento Kings overcame an 18-point deficit to beat the Golden State Warriors 123-117 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan scores 32 points in the Kings' 123-117 comeback victory over the Warriors

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 25 points, Jayson Tatum added 24 and the Boston Celtics rallied past the Los Angeles Clippers 117-113 in overtime on Wednesday night when both teams were missing key players.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown and Tatum lead Celtics past Clippers 117-113 in overtime with both teams missing starters
